Sentence: She will finish the report tomorrow.
She : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb «will finish»
will : auxiliary verb, marks simple future tense
finish : main verb, base form, indicates the action
the : definite article, specifies the noun «report»
report : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb «finish»
tomorrow : adverb of time, indicates when the action occurs

Sentence: They are going to visit Paris next week.
They : pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb «are going»
are : auxiliary verb, part of the «be going to» future construction
going : main verb, present participle, part of the «be going to» future construction
to : preposition, introduces the infinitive verb «visit»
visit : main verb, base form, indicates the action
Paris : proper noun, name of a city, direct object of the verb «visit»
next : adjective, modifies the noun «week»
week : common noun, singular, part of the time phrase

Sentence: I have seen that movie three times.
I : pronoun, first person singular, subject of the verb «have seen»
have : auxiliary verb, marks present perfect tense
seen : main verb, past participle of «see», indicates completed action
that : demonstrative adjective, specifies the noun «movie»
movie : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb «have seen»
three : cardinal number, quantifies the noun «times»
times : common noun, plural, indicates frequency

Sentence: He will not attend the meeting later.
He : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb «will attend»
will : auxiliary verb, marks simple future tense
not : adverb, negates the verb phrase
attend : main verb, base form, indicates the action
the : definite article, specifies the noun «meeting»
meeting : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb «attend»
later : adverb of time, indicates when the action occurs

Sentence: We have lived in this house for ten years.
We : pronoun, first person plural, subject of the verb «have lived»
have : auxiliary verb, marks present perfect tense
lived : main verb, past participle of «live», indicates duration up to now
in : preposition, introduces the location
this : demonstrative adjective, specifies the noun «house»
house : common noun, singular, object of the preposition «in»
for : preposition, introduces the duration
ten : cardinal number, quantifies the noun «years»
years : common noun, plural, object of the preposition «for»

Sentence: Sarah is going to buy a new car soon.
Sarah : proper noun, name of a person, subject of the verb «is going»
is : auxiliary verb, part of the «be going to» future construction
going : main verb, present participle, part of the «be going to» future construction
to : preposition, introduces the infinitive verb «buy»
buy : main verb, base form, indicates the action
a : indefinite article, introduces the noun «car»
new : adjective, describes the noun «car»
car : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb «buy»
soon : adverb of time, indicates when the action occurs

Sentence: You will understand the lesson eventually.
You : pronoun, second person, subject of the verb «will understand»
will : auxiliary verb, marks simple future tense
understand : main verb, base form, indicates the action
the : definite article, specifies the noun «lesson»
lesson : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb «understand»
