Sentence: They have written five emails today.
They : pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb «have written»
have : auxiliary verb, marks present perfect tense
written : main verb, past participle of «write», indicates completed action
five : cardinal number, quantifies the noun «emails»
emails : common noun, plural, direct object of the verb «have written»
