Sentence: My brother has broken his arm twice.
My : possessive adjective, modifies the noun «brother»
brother : common noun, singular, subject of the verb «has broken»
has : auxiliary verb, marks present perfect tense
broken : main verb, past participle of «break», indicates completed action
his : possessive adjective, modifies the noun «arm»
arm : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb «has broken»
twice : adverb of frequency, indicates how many times

Sentence: It is going to rain this afternoon.
It : pronoun, third person singular, impersonal subject of the verb «is going»
is : auxiliary verb, part of the «be going to» future construction
going : main verb, present participle, part of the «be going to» future construction
to : preposition, introduces the infinitive verb «rain»
rain : main verb, base form, indicates the weather action
this : demonstrative adjective, specifies the noun «afternoon»
afternoon : common noun, singular, adverbial phrase of time

Sentence: The students will pass the exam easily.
The : definite article, specifies the noun «students»
