pass : main verb, base form, indicates the action
the : definite article, specifies the noun «exam»
exam : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb «pass»
easily : adverb of manner, describes how the action is performed

Sentence: She has forgotten her keys again.
She : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb «has forgotten»
has : auxiliary verb, marks present perfect tense
forgotten : main verb, past participle of «forget», indicates completed action
her : possessive adjective, modifies the noun «keys»
keys : common noun, plural, direct object of the verb «has forgotten»
