Sentence: I have never been to Japan before.
I : pronoun, first person singular, subject of the verb «have been»
have : auxiliary verb, marks present perfect tense
never : adverb of frequency, negates the experience
been : main verb, past participle of «be», indicates existence or visit
to : preposition, introduces the destination
Japan : proper noun, name of a country, object of the preposition «to»
before : adverb of time, indicates prior experience
